    <div class="attendance-overview-help">
                   
                   <p>The <span style="font-weight:bold;">Manual Override</span> page enables you to manually override the attendance of an employee. You can revise the attendance<br/> value based on <span style="font-style:italic;">employee</span> or <span style="font-style:italic;">date</span>. To do so, you need to revise the attendance value in the <span style="font-weight:bold;">Override</span> column. Your changes are<br/> reflected on the Attendance Muster page. </p>
                   <p>Explore greytHR by <span style="color: #1fb6ff;cursor:pointer;">Help-Doc</span>, watching <span style="color: #1fb6ff;cursor:pointer;">How-to Videos</span> and <span style="color: #1fb6ff;cursor:pointer;">FAQ</span>.</p>
